Even if a woman does have access to contraception or reproductive health, she might not have access to safe and legal abortions.

- Save the Children says that Boko Haram Violence has forced 2.3 million children out of school, millions more don’t have access to quality education even if they aren’t affected by the conflict. Conditions have been made worse by a Nigerian government child protection ban which has failed to protect adolescents and girls from sexual assault, rape, and forced marriage.

- The number of children being recruited by Boko Haram has increased by 150% since 2018, from 760 - 1,900, and frighteningly, 1 in 4 children are below 10 years-old. The recruitment of minors by militant groups has become incredibly common.

- Nigeria has the world’s second-highest prevalence of FGM after Djibouti. According to WHO data, 30 % of Nigeria’s young female population is estimated to have undergone FGM, with Gombe having the highest prevalence and Kano the lowest.

- D. Honour: Child marriage rates in the north are doubled the national average. In the northeast Nigeria and Cameroon region 72% of girls are married by 19 years old.
